    <h2 id="how-it-works">How Centrifugal Oil Purification Works</h2>
    <p>
      A <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">disc stack centrifuge</a> spins contaminated oil at high G-force, separating solids and water from the clean oil phase. Unlike filters that clog and require frequent element changes, centrifuges operate continuously with minimal consumables. The separated sludge is ejected automatically, while purified oil returns to the machine sump or reservoir.
    </p>
    <p>
      For metalworking applications, this means uninterrupted production. Dolphin systems can be configured as inline units processing oil directly from machine sumps, or as kidney-loop systems that continuously polish a central reservoir. Our <a href="/centrifuge-repair-and-service/">service team</a> provides full installation support and ongoing maintenance.
    </p>

    <h2 id="benefits">Key Benefits</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Extended fluid life</strong> — Reduce oil replacement frequency by 3–5x, cutting procurement and disposal costs significantly.</li>
      <li><strong>Improved part quality</strong> — Clean cutting fluid means better surface finishes, tighter tolerances, and fewer rejects.</li>
      <li><strong>Lower disposal costs</strong> — Less spent oil means fewer hazardous waste pickups and lower regulatory burden.</li>
      <li><strong>Reduced downtime</strong> — Continuous purification eliminates batch processing delays and filter change stoppages.</li>
      <li><strong>Consistent thermal performance</strong> — Clean quench oil delivers uniform cooling rates for repeatable heat treatment results.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Mid-Page CTA -->
    <div class="not-prose my-10 bg-gold/10 border border-gold/40 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-2">Tired of Frequent Oil Replacements and Disposal Costs?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Cutting oil centrifuge systems pay for themselves in 6–18 months. Send us a sample of your oil — we'll test it and size the right centrifuge to maximize your fluid life.</p>
